feature_buffer = np.zeros(len(contact_feature_cols), dtype=np.float32)
# Fill in-place, then pass directly to model.predict()
2. Feature pruning using importances — after profiling, run this once on your trained model to identify which features matter:
pythonimportances = contact_model.feature_importances_
low_value = [contact_feature_cols[i] for i, v in enumerate(importances) if v < 0.005]
print(f"Can drop {len(low_value)} features: {low_value}")
Features below 0.5% importance contribute nothing to accuracy but cost compute every cycle. You can retrain with a reduced feature set, or just zero them out at inference time.
3. Reduce Isolation Forest estimators — you don't need to retrain. When you export the model, prune it:
